=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
Answer: Step 1: Start from 3-nitrophenylacetic acid (O2N–C6H4–CH2CO2H); convert it to the Weinreb amide 3-nitrophenylacetyl N-methoxy-N-methylamide (e.g., SOCl2, then MeNHOMe). | Step 2: Add MeMgBr to the Weinreb amide to stop at the methyl ketone, giving 1-(3-nitrophenyl)propan-2-one (O2N–C6H4–CH2COCH3). | Step 3: Reduce the nitro group (H2/Pd-C or Fe/HCl) to obtain 3-aminobenzyl methyl ketone, H2N–C6H4–CH2COCH3. | Step 4: Couple this aniline with benzyl isocyanate (PhCH2NCO) to form the unsymmetrical urea, yielding the target CC(=O)Cc1cccc(NC(=O)NCc2ccccc2)c1.

